<list>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <b>1991</b></entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

The watermark of the three lions is visible when the note is horizontal, but springs to life when the note is held against the light. The watermark is in two parts on the edges of the note.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Each note contains a security thread.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

The portraits are printed in the main colour of the note and their raised surface can be felt with the fingertips.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Each note has an individual serial number. The horizontal number on the left is printed in black and the vertical number on the right is printed in a different colour on each denomination.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

When the note is held at an angle to the light, the denomination of the note can be seen.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <b>1994</b></entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

New colour tints have been used in these areas.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Silver ink has been incorporated into the note.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

A new style serial number appears on the right-hand side.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

When the note is held up to the light, printed areas on the back of the note fill the unprinted areas on the front of the note.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

The colour of the ink in this area changes when the note is viewed from different angles.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <b>1996</b></entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Hologram featuring a swallow and the value '500'.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

A new hand-engraved portrait of Carl Robert Jakobson.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

A windowed thread with small text reading '500/EP'. The thread appears as a row of small silver dashes on the front surface of the note, but when the note is held up to the light it can be seen as a continuous line.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

When the note is held up to the light, printed areas on the back of the note fill unprinted areas on the front of the note to form the value '500'.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Silver ink has been incorporated into the note.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

New colour tints have been used in these areas.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

New signatures and date.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <b>2000</b></entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Portrait watermark.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Diffraction foil with microtext boarder (Exelgram).</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Dark security thread with transparent text "500EEK EESTI PANK".</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Tactile intaglio printed elements.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Microprint, repeated text "CARL ROBERT JAKOBSON".</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Microprint, repeated "500" within denomination numerals.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Latent number "500".</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Latent lettering "EP".</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Signatures (President of Eesti Pank, Chairman of the Board).</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Three lions printed with silver ink.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Anti-copier line structure.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Recognition sign for the visually handicapped.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Number "500" appears when the note is held up to the light.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

UV-fluorescent fibres.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

UV-fluorescent motif ("Sakala") and security thread.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

UV-fluorescent block bearing denomination number.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Serial numbers.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Variable ink element with magenta-to-green color shift.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

Hidden image, visible through a special lens.</entry>
</list>

</p>
